There are two methods of making records unavailable in the system: One is to delete the record, the other is to de-activate the record. A de-activated record is not available for selection, but available for reports. There are two reasons for de-activating and not deleting records: (1) The system requires the record for audit purposes. (2) The record is referenced by other records. Where inventory should be picked from first

The Relative Priority indicates the location to pick from first if an product is stored in more than one location. (100 = highest priority, 0 = lowest). For outgoing shipments, the location is picked with the highest priority where the entire quantity can be shipped from. If there is no location, the location with the highest priority is used. The Priority is ignored for products with Guarantee Date (always the oldest first) or if a specific instance is selected. Incoming receipts are stored at the location with the highest priority, if not explicitly selected.

Where inventory should be picked from first

The Relative Priority indicates the location to pick from first if an product is stored in more than one location. (100 = highest priority, 0 = lowest). For outgoing shipments, the location is picked with the highest priority where the entire quantity can be shipped from. If there is no location, the location with the highest priority is used. The Priority is ignored for products with Guarantee Date (always the oldest first) or if a specific instance is selected. Incoming receipts are stored at the location with the highest priority, if not explicitly selected.
